<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="411" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1854,2023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1854,1879]" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer approximately rectangular, not narrowing apically, ventral margin with a preapical membranous lobe with microsetae on apex (
<figureCitation box="[651,752,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,183,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1382,173,1739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Xiqilliba bellator Kramer: 1, 3 – 12, male holotype; 2, male, color variation: 1 – 2, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, head, frontal view; 4, head and pronotum, lateral view; 5, forewing; 6, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 7, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 8, subgenital plates, ventral view; 9, style, lateral view; 10, connective and styles, dorsal view; 11, aedeagus, lateral view; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">
Figs 6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,736,1890,1915]" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">–</emphasis>
7
</figureCitation>
). Style arched, without strong basal curve, with small apical spine curved ventrally and microsetae on entire lateral inner margin, giving it a serrate aspect (
<figureCitation box="[1301,1422,1926,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,183,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1382,173,1739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Xiqilliba bellator Kramer: 1, 3 – 12, male holotype; 2, male, color variation: 1 – 2, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, head, frontal view; 4, head and pronotum, lateral view; 5, forewing; 6, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 7, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 8, subgenital plates, ventral view; 9, style, lateral view; 10, connective and styles, dorsal view; 11, aedeagus, lateral view; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">
Figs 9 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1378,1392,1926,1951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">–</emphasis>
10
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus shaft with apical third curved dorsally and without processes (
<figureCitation box="[975,1104,1962,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,183,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1382,173,1739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Xiqilliba bellator Kramer: 1, 3 – 12, male holotype; 2, male, color variation: 1 – 2, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, head, frontal view; 4, head and pronotum, lateral view; 5, forewing; 6, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 7, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 8, subgenital plates, ventral view; 9, style, lateral view; 10, connective and styles, dorsal view; 11, aedeagus, lateral view; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">
Figs 11 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1059,1073,1962,1987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">–</emphasis>
12
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube with pair of long basal processes, narrowing towards apex, with sharp apices crossing inside genital capsule (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1279,1998,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,183,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1382,173,1739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Xiqilliba bellator Kramer: 1, 3 – 12, male holotype; 2, male, color variation: 1 – 2, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, head, frontal view; 4, head and pronotum, lateral view; 5, forewing; 6, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 7, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 8, subgenital plates, ventral view; 9, style, lateral view; 10, connective and styles, dorsal view; 11, aedeagus, lateral view; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">
Figs 6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1249,1263,1998,2023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="411">–</emphasis>
7
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
