<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="413" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,444,1421,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,1421,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Holotype</typeStatus>
condition.
</emphasis>
Antennal flagella broken. Thorax ventrally glued to the entomological triangle. Forewings and left hind wing in perfect condition, right hind wing broken apically. Fore legs, medium legs and left hind leg in perfect state of conservation, not broken but glued to the entomological triangle; right hind leg broken, tibia and tarsi glued to the entomological triangle. Abdomen dissected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1566,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Variations.</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[402,498,1567,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">paratype</typeStatus>
with brown markings of crown reduced, smaller than in 
<typeStatus box="[1139,1240,1566,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">holotype</typeStatus>
, and without pair of brown stains close to anterior margin, but with transverse stripe dark-brown to black on anterior margin of crown; central mark of crown dark-brown to black (
<figureCitation box="[732,800,1638,1663]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,183,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1382,173,1739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Xiqilliba bellator Kramer: 1, 3 – 12, male holotype; 2, male, color variation: 1 – 2, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, head, frontal view; 4, head and pronotum, lateral view; 5, forewing; 6, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 7, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 8, subgenital plates, ventral view; 9, style, lateral view; 10, connective and styles, dorsal view; 11, aedeagus, lateral view; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion box="[821,903,1638,1663]" country="Oman" name="Al Wusta" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Central</collectingRegion>
mark of pronotum also dark-brown to black, of irregular form, with strong constriction close to anterior margin; posterior margin with brown transverse stripe (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1711,1736]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,183,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1382,173,1739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Xiqilliba bellator Kramer: 1, 3 – 12, male holotype; 2, male, color variation: 1 – 2, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, head, frontal view; 4, head and pronotum, lateral view; 5, forewing; 6, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 7, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 8, subgenital plates, ventral view; 9, style, lateral view; 10, connective and styles, dorsal view; 11, aedeagus, lateral view; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Basal half of forewing, opaque, only apical half hyaline; remainder of clavus brown to black. Legs yellow to light-brown.
</paragraph>
